00:37:07.076 --> 00:37:10.756
likely that the mature markers are being expressed on some

621
00:37:10.796 --> 00:37:14.476
cells that have immature markers, because we're defining the most immature cells as

622
00:37:14.556 --> 00:37:17.996
lineage negative. So I think one of the challenges here as we move, for example,

623
00:37:18.016 --> 00:37:21.966
from classical flow to spectral flow, is to begin to ask if

624
00:37:22.016 --> 00:37:25.406
this is really myeloid maturation or myeloid marker

625
00:37:25.536 --> 00:37:29.286
expression on an otherwise immature population, which might have more of a

626
00:37:29.316 --> 00:37:33.066
mixed state, if you will. But that's important

627
00:37:33.116 --> 00:37:36.936
because that fits with the clinical observation that we see in RAS

628
00:37:36.976 --> 00:37:40.596
mutant leukemia, and I won't tell you about today, but a lot of work, for example,

629
00:37:40.616 --> 00:37:44.476
by Craig Jordan and his former postdoc, Courtney Jones, now at the

630
00:37:44.516 --> 00:37:48.456
University of Cincinnati with Dan Paglia, has shown that, one, RAS mutations tend

631
00:37:48.496 --> 00:37:52.416
to correlate with this, and two, in addition to IDH inhibitor resistance, you

