00:43:28.548 --> 00:43:30.568
leukemias that have a RAS wild type.

728
00:43:31.108 --> 00:43:34.628
ELOVL1, I didn't show you this data, does synergize with IDH

729
00:43:34.668 --> 00:43:38.608
inhibition, suggesting potentially you might get a combination strategy,

730
00:43:38.628 --> 00:43:41.558
and the catalytic activity is required for this function.

731
00:43:42.728 --> 00:43:46.488
So what's the mechanism that underlies this association between NRAS

732
00:43:46.528 --> 00:43:50.428
oncogenic capacity and ELOVL1 dependency, at least in these

733
00:43:50.528 --> 00:43:54.128
leukemias? And so we know that very long-chain fatty acid

734
00:43:54.208 --> 00:43:57.668
processing is important in a number of biological processes.

735
00:43:57.988 --> 00:44:01.588
One of them is the peroxisome, and the other would be thinking about

736
00:44:01.628 --> 00:44:05.248
sphingolipid to ceramide, and a number of other

737
00:44:05.268 --> 00:44:08.908
pathways. And so we first depleted core

738
00:44:08.968 --> 00:44:12.128
peroxisome members, and the short answer was no dependency.

